<TITLE> Mamun's wife surrenders to court, refused bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 6 (bdnews24.com)  Controversial businessman Giasuddin Al Mamun's wife, who was convicted in absentia for possessing illegally obtained wealth, surrendered to the court on Tuesday and was refused bail Shahina Yasmin handed herself into to Judge Jesmine Anwar of the Special Judge's Court-4. The Anticorruption Commission filed the case in May 2007 against Mamun and Shahina for possessing wealth beyond their known legal sources amounting to Tk 111 crore. A special judge's court sentenced Mamun on Mar 27, 2008 to 10 years in jail and imposed a fine of Tk 10 lakh. Shahina, who was tried in absentia, received three years in jail and a fine of Tk 5 lakh. The court had said that her punishment would take effect from the day she was arrested or surrendered to the court. Mamun secured bail from the High Court in the case.
